text: On this document, it sounds like voting and a take on time keeping/agenda were prevalent feature requests from the facilitators in both NY and Paris. Do we have a preference over which one we should feature alongside _Questions_ and _Beacons_ in tomorrows design jam?
<@U0B9N0HF0|rob> shared a file: <https://uncorked.slack.com/files/rob/F0FRU8E64/designjamtenativeagenda|Design Jam Tenative Agenda>

Follow-up question here as well. In the outline for the exercise, it states to have the Google folks them to take a picture of their sketch with their phone and post it to a google doc/deck. Thinking that may be tough from the phone or at least take some explaining. Can anyone think of an alternative service that the BL folks could use to post their sketches to a shared document from their phones?

Think I have answer. I’ve created a folder in Google Drive which is easy to share to from iPhone sharing options. Assume it should be even easier on an Android (any Android users here who can confirm?).

One thing we’ll want to decide though, is with the teams each being remote, do we ask them to print the previous teams sketch/efforts, quickly recreate them or just keep them in their mind when drawing the new efforts?
